% bench_interpreter.trx -- main interpreter-loop dispatch throughput.
%
% Each inner iteration executes four operators that all dispatch through
% the main interpreter loop: push integer(1), push integer(2), add, pop.
% The integer adds exercise the arithmetic shim as well as the dispatch
% proper, so the number is a fair "what is a representative op/sec" figure
% rather than a best-case empty dispatch.
%
% Outer `repeat` drives the work.  Total operators executed per run =
% 4 * N (plus a tiny constant for the repeat/def setup).  Tweak N to aim
% at a ~3-5 second wall-clock run on target hardware.

/N 25000000 def
N { 1 2 add pop } repeat
